args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Victor's adventurer story.
The enemy mages aren't letting up!\nWe can only hold them off for so long!
Those mages' mana will run dry before\nlong, and they will be forced to make way\nfor the forces coming up behind them.
Our spies are already at work slowing\nthat rear unit's arrival. So as soon as\nthe mages are out of mana, we strike.
B-but what if we can't hold out that long?
You can either die here, soldier, or live to\nsee your fiancée again.
I... I swore I would give her this ring!\nI have to survive!
Then believe in my plan.\nWe WILL win this battle.
Rrgh... We've lost the advantage.\nRETREAAAT! Join up with the rear unit!
You can't beat us at close range.\nThis battle is ours!
You could never match the might of\nSvenitla.
And we will make you rue the folly that\nmade you try!

The military nation of Svenitla sits in one of
the coldest regions of North Grastaea, clashing
constantly with its neighbors over the continent's
limited natural resources.
His Majesty is most pleased with your\nperformance, Commander. It will no\ndoubt bring prosperity to the nation.
The losses we suffered are negligible\nwhen one considers what was gained.
You have proven yourself most capable\nindeed—unlike your peers.
I am merely performing my duty, sir.
Heh. And modest as well. We trust you\ngreatly, Commander. Few could achieve\nwhat you have with such sparse resources.
War exists to bolster the economy.\nA soldier's job is to maximize profits\nwith the minimum investment.
...Forgive me, sir, but if that will be all,\nI have other business to attend to.
A feast is soon to begin in honor of\nyour victory. Surely your business\ncan wait until later?
I am afraid it's a most pressing\nengagement.
Do you mean to suggest you have\nsomewhere more important to be\nthan at a feast with HIS MAJESTY?
He wanted very badly to give you this\nhimself.
No... H-he promised we'd be married when\nhe returned! He... He promised... *sob*
As his commanding officer, I accept full\nresponsibility. I am truly sorry.
Tell me... What did he die for?
What did he give his life for?!\nTell me!
Your fiancé brought salvation to this\ncountry.
I'm the commander's adjutant.\nAllow me to speak on her behalf.

The war we just fought secured our
nation new land and natural resources.
These will in turn make our home all
the more prosperous.
Many of our people are still mired in\npoverty, but your beloved's sacrifice\nwill help lift them out.
Your tongue is as silver as ever, Joachim.
When it needs to be, yes. And when the\nalternative is a truth as ugly as the one\nwe face, a little silver goes a long way.
Our sacrifices mean nothing, in the end.\nThe rich simply get richer.
We risk our lives time after time,\nfighting against all odds for a\nfarcical cause. It's getting tiring.
Enough, Joachim. As soldiers, our place\nis on the battlefield. Anything that follows\nis not our concern. Now, why are you here?
Ah, right. We've got new orders in\nfrom HQ.
They want us to visit the Dyrenell Empire\nas emissaries, with the hope of forming\na military alliance.
And here's the kicker: to keep costs to\na minimum, they're sending just the\ntwo of us. Alone.
That's the empire to the south with designs\nto expand, yes?
Right. And I don't know if you've heard,\nbut they're pretty much the most evil\nforce around these days.
Be that as it may, we have our orders.\nBegin departure preparations at once.\nI will be along shortly.
What will you be doing in the meantime?
I want to linger here awhile.\nAlone.
If we can secure an alliance with Dyrenell,\nit should reduce the burden on our own\nmilitary. That should mean fewer deaths.
It's an enticing proposition, but I can't\nhelp feeling some trepidation about\njourneying south.
I had hoped to never see his face again...
